  100
  
    
	// Note: going to skip the first value, it is noise as the time


  		





  
  101
  
    
	// delta is wrong

  103

  108

  110

#include <math.h>


  		





  
  23
  
    

  		





  
  24
  
    
const int CadencePin = 3;                         // pin used to measure cadence


  		





  
  25
  
    
const int DirectionPin = 2;                       // pin to read direction


  		





  
  26
  
    
const int NumPoles = 12;                          // number of magnetic pole pairs on the tone ring


  		





  
  27
  
    

  		





  
  28
  
    
volatile unsigned long LastStepTime;              // last time the step sensor was triggered


  		





  
  29
  
    
volatile float SensedDeltaT;                      // deltaT as calculated during interrupt calls


  		





  
  30
  
    
volatile boolean WalkingForward;                  // walking direction state


  		





  
  31
  
    

  		





  
  32
  
    
float Cadence;                                    // pedalling speed


  		





  
  33
  
    

  		





  
  34
  
    

  		





  
  35
  
    
// common function to attach/detach interrupts


  		





  
  36
  
    
void EnableSensors(unsigned int enable) {


  		





  
  37
  
    
  if (enable) {


  		





  
  38
  
    
    attachInterrupt(digitalPinToInterrupt(CadencePin), DetectCadence, FALLING);


  		





  
  39
  
    
    //attachInterrupt(DirectionInterruptNumber, DetermineDirection, FALLING);


  		





  
  40
  
    
  }


  		





  
  41
  
    
  else {


  		





  
  42
  
    
    detachInterrupt(digitalPinToInterrupt(CadencePin));


  		





  
  43
  
    
    //detachInterrupt(DirectionInterruptNumber);


  		





  
  44
  
    
  }


  		





  
  45
  
    
}


  		





  
  46
  
    

  		





  
  47
  
    
// interrupt function used to measure cadence


  		





  
  48
  
    
void DetectCadence() {


  		





  
  49
  
    
  unsigned long currentTime = millis();


  		





  
  50
  
    
  SensedDeltaT = (currentTime - LastStepTime);


  		





  
  51
  
    
  LastStepTime = currentTime;


  		





  
  52
  
    
  WalkingForward = digitalRead(DirectionPin);  // CCW is forward


  		





  
  53
  
    
}


  		





  
  54
  
    

  		





  
  55
  
    
// resets walking state variables, used when holoseat is disabled


  		





  
  56
  
    
void InitializeWalkingVariables() {


  		





  
  57
  
    
  Cadence = 0.0;


  		





  
  58
  
    
  SensedDeltaT = 5000;            // initialize sensed deltaT (and the value used to compute it, LastStepTime) to 5 seconds in the past


  		





  
  59
  
    
  LastStepTime = millis() - 5000; // as above


  		





  
  60
  
    
  WalkingForward = true;  


  		





  
  61
  
    
}


  		





  
  62
  
    

  		





  
  63
  
    
// the setup function runs once when you press reset or power the board


  		





  
  64
  
    
void setup() {


  		





  
  65
  
    
  pinMode(DirectionPin, INPUT);


  		





  
  66
  
    
  pinMode(CadencePin, INPUT);


  		





  
  67
  
    
  InitializeWalkingVariables();


  		





  
  68
  
    
  EnableSensors(true);


  		





  
  69
  
    
  Serial.begin(57600); 


  		





  
  70
  
    
  Serial.println("r"); // send ready signal


  		





  
  71
  
    
}


  		





  
  72
  
    

  		





  
  73
  
    
// the loop function runs over and over again forever


  		





  
  74
  
    
void loop() {


  		





  
  75
  
    
  delay(10);


  		





  
  76
  
    
  EnableSensors(false);


  		





  
  77
  
    

  		





  
  78
  
    
  // calculate the Cadence


  		





  
  79
  
    
  unsigned long currentTime = millis();


  		





  
  80
  
    
  float localDeltaT = (currentTime - LastStepTime);  


  		





  
  81
  
    
  float deltaT = max(SensedDeltaT, localDeltaT)/1000; // in seconds


  		





  
  82
  
    
  Cadence = round(60.0/deltaT/NumPoles);  // in RPM


  		





  
  83
  
    
  


  		





  
  84
  
    
  if (WalkingForward)


  		





  
  85
  
    
    Serial.print("+");


  		





  
  86
  
    
  else


  		





  
  87
  
    
    Serial.print("-");


  		





  
  88
  
    

  		





  
  89
  
    
  Serial.print((int)Cadence);


  		





  
  90
  
    
  Serial.println("");  


  		





  
  91
  
    
  EnableSensors(true);                  


  		





  
  92
  
    
}

# This example is meant to be used from within the CadQuery module of FreeCAD.


  		





  
  14
  
    
import cadquery


  		





  
  15
  
    
import math


  		





  
  16
  
    
from Helpers import show


  		





  
  17
  
    

  		





  
  18
  
    
# The dimensions of the box. These can be modified rather than changing the


  		





  
  19
  
    
# object's code directly.


  		





  
  20
  
    
radius = 2.5 *1.04 # correction factor for J's 3D printer


  		





  
  21
  
    
halfWidth = 1.5 * 1.07 # correction factor for J's 3D printer


  		





  
  22
  
    
halfHeight = math.sqrt(math.pow(radius, 2) - math.pow(halfWidth, 2))


  		





  
  23
  
    

  		





  
  24
  
    
# The dimensions of the box. These can be modified rather than changing the


  		





  
  25
  
    
# object's code directly.


  		





  
  26
  
    
length = 20.0


  		





  
  27
  
    
height = 100.0


  		





  
  28
  
    
thickness = 3.0


  		





  
  29
  
    
post_dia = 4.9


  		





  
  30
  
    
post_height = 3.0


  		





  
  31
  
    
post_placement = height - 26.0 - post_dia


  		





  
  32
  
    

  		





  
  33
  
    
# Create a box based on the dimensions above and add a 22mm center hole


  		





  
  34
  
    
#result = cadquery.Workplane("XY").box(length, height, thickness) \


  		





  
  35
  
    
#    .faces(">Z").workplane().hole(center_hole_dia)


  		





  
  36
  
    
# r.faces(">Z").workplane()


  		





  
  37
  
    

  		





  
  38
  
    
r = cadquery.Workplane("XY").box(length, height, thickness)


  		





  
  39
  
    

  		





  
  40
  
    
r = r.faces(">Z").workplane().line(0, post_placement, True)\


  		





  
  41
  
    
    .circle(post_dia/2).extrude(post_height).faces(">Z").workplane()\


  		





  
  42
  
    
        .line(0, -2 * post_placement, True).circle(post_dia/2).extrude(-post_height)


  		





  
  43
  
    

  		





  
  44
  
    
r = r.cut(cadquery.Workplane("XY").line(halfWidth, 0, True).line(0, halfHeight)\


  		





  
  45
  
    
    .threePointArc((0, radius), (-halfWidth, halfHeight)).line(0, -halfHeight)\


  		





  
  46
  
    
        .mirrorX().extrude(thickness))


  		





  
  47
  
    

  		





  
  48
  
    
r = r.cut(cadquery.Workplane("XY").line(halfWidth, 0, True).line(0, halfHeight)\


  		





  
  49
  
    
    .threePointArc((0, radius), (-halfWidth, halfHeight)).line(0, -halfHeight)\


  		





  
  50
  
    
        .mirrorX().extrude(-thickness))


  		





  
  51
  
    

  		





  
  52
  
    

  		





  
  53
  
    
# Render the solid


  		





  
  54
  
    
show(r)

{

Applies to IE10+ and Firefox. Null for the largest (last) breakpoint.\n// The maximum value is calculated as the minimum of the next one less 0.1.\n//\n//    >> breakpoint-max(sm, (xs: 0, sm: 576px, md: 768px, lg: 992px, xl: 1200px))\n//    767px\n@function breakpoint-max($name, $breakpoints: $grid-breakpoints) {\n  $next: breakpoint-next($name, $breakpoints);\n  @return if($next, breakpoint-min($next, $breakpoints) - 1px, null);\n}\n\n// Returns a blank string if smallest breakpoint, otherwise returns the name with a dash infront.\n// Useful for making responsive utilities.\n//\n//    >> breakpoint-infix(xs, (xs: 0, sm: 576px, md: 768px, lg: 992px, xl: 1200px))\n//    \"\"  (Returns a blank string)\n//    >> breakpoint-infix(sm, (xs: 0, sm: 576px, md: 768px, lg: 992px, xl: 1200px))\n//    \"-sm\"\n@function breakpoint-infix($name, $breakpoints: $grid-breakpoints) {\n  @return if(breakpoint-min($name, $breakpoints) == null, \"\", \"-#{$name}\");\n}\n\n// Media of at least the minimum breakpoint width. No query for the smallest breakpoint.\n// Makes the @content apply to the given breakpoint and wider.\n@mixin media-breakpoint-up($name, $breakpoints: $grid-breakpoints) {\n  $min: breakpoint-min($name, $breakpoints);\n  @if $min {\n    @media (min-width: $min) {\n      @content;\n    }\n  } @else {\n    @content;\n  }\n}\n\n// Media of at most the maximum breakpoint width. // Prevent columns from collapsing when empty\n    padding-right: ($gutter / 2);\n    padding-left:  ($gutter / 2);\n  }\n\n  @each $breakpoint in map-keys($breakpoints) {\n    $infix: breakpoint-infix($breakpoint, $breakpoints);\n\n    // Allow columns to stretch full width below their breakpoints\n    @for $i from 1 through $columns {\n      .col#{$infix}-#{$i} {\n        @extend %grid-column;\n      }\n    }\n    .col#{$infix},\n    .col#{$infix}-auto {\n      @extend %grid-column;\n    }\n\n    @include media-breakpoint-up($breakpoint, $breakpoints) {\n      // Provide basic `.col-{bp}` classes for equal-width flexbox columns\n      .col#{$infix} {\n        flex-basis: 0;\n        flex-grow: 1;\n        max-width: 100%;\n      }\n      .col#{$infix}-auto {\n        flex: 0 0 auto;\n        width: auto;\n        max-width: none;
